{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310)."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"]}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"symbolKind":"property","externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","title":"overlayBounds"},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon.","type":"text"}],"title":"MLNOverlay"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"overlayBounds","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"abstract":[{